    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen splitting a terminal window in terminal mode, `WinResized` is not triggered until user exit terminal mode.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following `minimal.lua` file:\r\n\r\n    ```lua\r\n    vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('WinResized', {\r\n      callback = function()\r\n        print('win resized: ' .. vim.inspect(vim.v.event.windows))\r\n      end\r\n    })\r\n\r\n    vim.keymap.set({ 'n', 't' }, '<M-s>', '<Cmd>split<CR>')\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n2. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\r\n3. Split window in normal mode, observe that the `win resized: ...` message appears immediately\r\n4. `:term`\r\n5. Split window in terminal mode using `<M-s>`, observe that there is not message shown\r\n6. Exit terminal mode, the message is shown.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`WinResized` event should trigger once the terminal is splitted.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-2085+g310fb2efc3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim's terminal use a completely different implementation\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.7.0-arch3-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.14.0-dev (94ede16e)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
